content:
I guess `write_output` doesn't need to concatenate to a buffer, re <@381789485777682434> comment -- It could still do something like this internally:

```c
HashState state;
void write_output(const uint8_t* output, size_t size) {
    hash_update(&state, output, size);
}

void on_program_exit() {
    uint8_t final_hash[32];
    hash_finalize(&state, final_hash);
    commit_public_input(final_hash);
}
```
